1. What is the purpose of HTML in web development?** 
HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language. It is the basic structure of every webpage on the 
internet. It gives the layout of the page by using elements like headings and paragraphs. 
Without HTML, a website cannot display any text or structure. Web browsers read HTML files to 
show the content correctly to users. It is the founda on of all web development. 
