**7. Explain the difference between absolute and rela ve URLs.** 
An absolute URL contains the complete internet address of a file or website. It always includes 
the protocol like h ps:// and the domain name. A rela ve URL points to a file path inside the 
same website project. It does not include the domain name, only the path from the current 
folder. Absolute URLs are best for linking to external websites. Rela ve URLs are perfect for 
connec ng your own local pages together. 
