**10. Explain the difference between GET and POST methods.** 
The GET method is used to request data from a specific server. It shows the sent data inside the 
website URL link address. Because of this, it is not safe for private info like passwords. The POST 
method is used to send data to a server to update a database. It hides the data inside the 
request body instead of the URL. Therefore, POST is much more secure for sensi ve user 
informa on. 
